Variation . Carapace length: males 4.9–7.2 (n= 35 ), females 4.4–7.4 (n= 36 ). Femur II: males 8.6–12 (n= 35 ), females 5.6–9.25 (n= 36 ). Picks in the palpal femur: 5–6 . Spermathecae branches: 15–18 . Genitalic morphology is variable in both sexes (
Figs 48–61
).

Distribution . Northeastern Brazil , in the states of Piauí, Ceará, Rio Grande do Norte, Paraíba, Pernambuco and Sergipe (
Fig. 166
).
